===========================================================================

OLDER NOTES (June 2001)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

I can only create a 2047-MB virtual machine.  But it only has to contain
the operating system; I can keep all data on the host and do networking.
Do not install to raw disk; OSes keep caches and do partial writes, so this
would lead to inconsistencies and data loss.
Or maybe I shouldn't worry about this at all and should dual-boot
or have a separate computer instead.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Installation on PC:
 * Answer questions:
    * no networking
    * disable CD autorun
 * Enable host-only networking
    * subnet = 172.16.198
 * Use configuration editor to add floppy later; this must be done with the
   floppy in the bay.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Installation on Linux:

Download from http://www.vmware.com/download/downloadlinux.html

http://www.vmware.com/support/linux/doc/install_config_linux.html

# Run this on the machine with the peripherals attached, not on a server.
## This "rpm" command segfaulted on meoptiplex, 12/4/2000.
## Instead, try from the tar file
## rpm -Uhv bin/src/vmware/VMware-2.0.3-799.i386.rpm
# Do this not as root
cd ~mernst/bin/src/vmware
tar zxf VMware-2.0.3-799.tar.gz
su
cd ~mernst/bin/src/vmware
cd vmware-distrib 
./vmware-install.pl

